{"id": "5379", "post": "<div class=\"post-5379 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-bulgaria tag-exclusive tag-openvz tag-sofia tag-vpsbg-eu\" id=\"post-5379\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/vpsbg-e4-80-6-55-month-512mb-ssd-openvz-vps-in-sofia-bulgaria/\" rel=\"bookmark\">VPSBG \u2013 \u20ac4.80 ($6.55) /month 512MB SSD OpenVZ VPS in Sofia, Bulgaria</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/bulgaria/\" rel=\"tag\">bulgaria</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/exclusive/\" rel=\"tag\">exclusive</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/sofia/\" rel=\"tag\">sofia</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/vpsbg-eu/\" rel=\"tag\">VPSBG.eu</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> June 23, 2014 @ 1:00 pm, by Maarten Kossen</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"https://www.vpsbg.eu/en/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTg4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDE4OCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/VPSBG_Offshore_VPS_hosting_in_Sofia_Bulgaria_-_2014-06-23_06.32.05-300x188.png.webp\" alt=\"VPSBG_Offshore_VPS_hosting_in_Sofia,_Bulgaria_-_2014-06-23_06.32.05\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\"></a>Rosen, from <a href=\"https://www.vpsbg.eu/en/\">VPSBG</a>, contacted us recently with an exclusive offer for LowEndBox readers for a VPS in Bulgaria! VPSBG is part of Solidex Ltd., which is a registered hosting company in Bulgaria (company registration number: 121175406). They have launched in April 2013 and have been working hard to grow ever since. Host nodes are Supermicro servers using Intel Xeon X3-1240v3 CPUs with speeds of 3.4 GHz+, 32GB&nbsp; or RAM, and&nbsp; Samsung Evo 840 SSDs in a RAID configuration. VPSBG claims not to oversell their nodes, which is a good thing. They are also the first host I see that uses OVZ Web Panel, rather than SolusVM, which makes this more interesting to try out. I haven\u2019t been able to find any reviews, so if you do give them a try, please let us know about it!</p><p><strong>The offer</strong></p><ul><li>512MB RAM</li><li>512MB vSwap</li><li>1 vCPU core</li><li>15GB SSD space</li><li>500GB bandwidth</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>IPv6 on request</li><li>OpenVZ/OVZ Web Panel</li><li>Coupon: <strong>leb20</strong></li><li>\u20ac4.80 ($6.55) /month</li><li><a href=\"https://www.vpsbg.eu/en/index.php?page=cp&amp;action=register\">Order here</a></li></ul><p><span id=\"more-5379\"></span></p><p>VPSBG accepts PayPal, bank transfer, Bitcoin, and Litecoin for payments. They have a 14-day refund policy but will deny a refund in cases of abuse. IRC is allowed, as are proxies and TOR (for private use only). Adult content is also allowed, as long as it does not violate any Bulgarian laws. Please read their full <a href=\"https://www.vpsbg.eu/en/index.php?page=terms-of-service\">Terms of Service</a> before ordering.</p><p><strong>Network Information</strong></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Neterra Datacenter, Sofia, Bulgaria</span><br>\nIP: 94.156.77.1<br>\nTest file: http://94.156.77.2/100MB.test</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-to